**Communication patterns**: "message", "chat", "email", "inbox", "compose", "reply", "contact", "call", "video call", "conversation"\
\
### Step 2: Detect Platform Context  \
Extract platform indicators:\
- **Mobile indicators**: "app", "mobile", "touch", "swipe", "on-the-go"\
- **Desktop indicators**: "web", "browser", "desktop", "keyboard", "mouse"\
- **Usage context**: Professional, personal, entertainment, utility\
\
### Step 3: Generate Actual Content\
Create real UI content that users would see in production apps for the extracted domain. Output actual text, not descriptions of text.\
\
## PLATFORM-APPROPRIATE NAVIGATION SPECIFICATION\
\
### Automatic Navigation Inclusion Rules\
When generating content specifications, **ALWAYS include appropriate navigation patterns** based on detected platform context, even when not explicitly requested by the user.\
\
### Mobile App Navigation Requirements\
For mobile-focused requests (detected through keywords like "app", "mobile", "touch", "swipe" or when context implies mobile usage):\
\
**MANDATORY Navigation Elements:**\
- **Top Navigation**: Always include header/app bar navigation\
- **Bottom Navigation**: Always include bottom tab navigation (unless explicitly stated otherwise)\
\
### Desktop/Web Navigation Requirements\
For desktop-focused requests (detected through keywords like "web", "browser", "desktop", "keyboard", "mouse"):\
\
**MANDATORY Navigation Elements:**\
- **Header Navigation**: Always include primary navigation bar\
- **Sidebar Navigation**: Include when appropriate for complex applications\
- **Breadcrumb Navigation**: Include for deep hierarchical content\
